Resource.message:
!!!Must use new config!!!

Added Notifications at top of screen
Added Config option Display type (0 = Both, 1 = Chat, 2 = Notification)
Added Config InstantNotifications uses ActorTick hook for instant notifications this also overrides SafeZoneNotificationCheckSeconds and needs a restart if changed
Added SafeZone Config EnterNotificationColour for setting the Notification and chat message when entering a safezone
Added SafeZone Config LeaveNotificationColour for setting the Notification and chat message when entering a safezone

[SPOILER="Plugin Developers Only"]
Added Api support now you can include SafeZone/Public/SafeZone.h
and use it include it in your own plugins like so

SafeZone::IsInSafeZone(const FVector Position); //check if a position is in a safezone
SafeZone::AddOnPlayerJoinLeaveCallBack(const FString& id, const std::function<void(AShooterPlayerController*, bool)>& callback); //calls a function you declared locally
SafeZone::RemoveOnPlayerJoinLeaveCallBack(const FString& id); //removes your callbacks when your plugin is unloaded


SafeZone::AddOnPlayerJoinLeaveCallBack Example:

void OnPlayerInOrOutOfSafeZone(AShooterPlayerController* Player, const bool IsInSafeZone)
{
    if(IsInSafeZone)
    {
        Log::GetLog()->warn("{} Is In the safezone", ArkApi::GetApiUtils().GetCharacterName(Player));
    }
    else
    {
        Log::GetLog()->warn("{} Is Not In the safezone", ArkApi::GetApiUtils().GetCharacterName(Player));
    }
}

SafeZone::AddOnPlayerJoinLeaveCallBack(&OnPlayerInOrOutOfSafeZone);[/SPOILER]

